001package com.technototes.path.command;
002
003import java.util.function.BiFunction;
004import java.util.function.Function;
005import java.util.function.Supplier;
006
007import com.acmerobotics.roadrunner.geometry.Pose2d;
008import com.acmerobotics.roadrunner.trajectory.Trajectory;
009import com.acmerobotics.roadrunner.trajectory.TrajectoryBuilder;
010
011import com.technototes.library.command.Command;
012import com.technototes.path.subsystem.MecanumDrivebaseSubsystem;
013
014public class TrajectoryCommand implements Command {
015    public Trajectory trajectory;
016    public MecanumDrivebaseSubsystem subsystem;
017
018    public TrajectoryCommand(MecanumDrivebaseSubsystem sub, Trajectory t) {
019        addRequirements(sub);
020        subsystem = sub;
021        trajectory = t;
022    }
023
024    public TrajectoryCommand(
025            MecanumDrivebaseSubsystem sub, Function<Function<Pose2d, TrajectoryBuilder>, Trajectory> t) {
026        addRequirements(sub);
027        subsystem = sub;
028        trajectory = t.apply(sub::trajectoryBuilder);
029    }
030
031    public TrajectoryCommand(MecanumDrivebaseSubsystem sub, Supplier<Trajectory> t) {
032        addRequirements(sub);
033        subsystem = sub;
034        trajectory = t.get();
035    }
036
037    public <T> TrajectoryCommand(
038            MecanumDrivebaseSubsystem sub, BiFunction<Function<Pose2d, TrajectoryBuilder>, T, Trajectory> t, T mux) {
039        addRequirements(sub);
040        subsystem = sub;
041        trajectory = t.apply(sub::trajectoryBuilder, mux);
042    }
043
044    public <T> TrajectoryCommand(MecanumDrivebaseSubsystem sub, Function<T, Trajectory> t, T mux) {
045        addRequirements(sub);
046        subsystem = sub;
047        trajectory = t.apply(mux);
048    }
049
050    @Override
051    public void initialize() {
052        subsystem.followTrajectoryAsync(trajectory);
053    }
054
055    @Override
056    public void execute() {
057        subsystem.update();
058    }
059
060    @Override
061    public boolean isFinished() {
062        return !subsystem.isBusy();
063    }
064
065    @Override
066    public void end(boolean cancel) {
067        if (cancel) subsystem.stop();
068    }
069}
